com.camerontec.catalys.fixtesttool.fix.channel

Class FIXMessageChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.fixtesttool.fix.channel.FIXMessageChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FIXEventSender, FIXMessageSender, Runnable

    public final class FIXMessageChannel
extends Object
implements FIXEventSender, Runnable
    Class which provides a channel for full duplex FIX message communication over a TCP/IP socket.

    This class does not implement the FIX transport protocol, it just provides basic send/receive capabilities. However, it is possible to supply an IFIXSessionStatePersister if resuming a FIX session is required across multiple TCP connections.

    This class is capable of both initiating and accepting FIX connections. The behaviour is governed by the properties supplied to the open(java.util.Properties) method.

    When the channel is an initiating channel it has elementary connection retry support.

    Messages sent via the channel are synchronous. That is, send(com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.IFIXMessage) does not return until the message is delivered to the underlying transport. Messages are persisted before being sent.

    Messages received via the channel are delivered in a single, dedicated thread under the control of the channel. The incoming message sequence number is persisted after the messages is delivered to and handled by the specified FIXEventListener.

    See Also:
    FIXEventSender

      • open

        public void open(Properties connectionProperties)
        Description copied from interface: FIXEventSender
        Send an event requesting that FIX connection according to the specified properties be opened.

        To open an accepting FIX connection specify the following property only:

        • FIXEventSender.LISTENPORT_PROPERTY

        To open an initiating FIX connection specify the following properties:

        • FIXEventSender.HOSTNAME_PROPERTY
        • FIXEventSender.PORT_PROPERTY
        • FIXEventSender.MAX_CONNECTION_ATTEMPTS (optional - if not specified behavior is implementation dependent)
        • FIXEventSender.CONNECTION_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS (optional - if not specified behavior is implementation dependent)
        Specified by:
        open in interface FIXEventSender
        Parameters:
        connectionProperties - Connection properties.
